<TITLE> Norway's sure-shot women win gold </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BEIJING, Aug 23 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Norway's women won Olympic handball gold on Saturday after hammering Russia 34-27 thanks to a superbly synchronised defence and drill-like attack. The tanned, smiling Norwegians skipped across the pitch in single file after their victory, waving a huge red-and-blue Norwegian flag. Russia took silver, while Korea won bronze. Norway raced ahead in the first half, at one point leading with 17 goals against Russia's 9, and their solid defence and relentless attack contrasted with the somewhat hesitant and scattered Russians. Russia tried to catch up, with top scorer Irina Bliznova sinking five shots into Norway's goal, but Norway still topped the first half 18-13. To a backdrop of Norwegian fans in red T-shirts, Linn-Kristin Riegelhuth and Else Lybekk led Norway's attack in the first half while powerful scorer Gro Hammerseng came into her own with a signature sure-shot later in the game. Even an impressive last-minute assault by the Russians  three goals in the 60th minutecould not save the day. Riegelhuth was the top scorer of the game with nine goals, why Lybekk followed closely behind with seven
